The paper deals with the analysis of time-varying networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the study of network structures and dynamics. The paper also involves statistical analysis and hypothesis testing, which are topics covered by cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Monte Carlo simulations suggests a focus on cs.SY (Systems and Control), while the use of a community graph model and stochastic blockmodel suggests a focus on cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
